		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm not sure where to put this, so move it as seen fit. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />
<br />
<br />Anyway, I would like to extract the FDS waveforms from lots of games that use it. The raw waveform. Raw. That means no holding the mic to the speakers. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> Now, I would rather not have to rip apart the PRG rom to find these waves, so is there any emulator or something that supports viewing the fds waveform from wherever it is in ram?
<br />
<br />Thanks

		

